COVID-19 Status

As of 8:53PM PT yesterday, over 1.5 million Canadians have tested positive for COVID-19. Sadly, 27 thousand have died.

In the last day, 4 thousand new infections were reported and 29 deaths. This is trending upwards.

Fortunately, 53.5 million doses of the vaccine have been administered. For those 12 years and older, 84% have their 1st shot and 76.6% are fully vaccinated!

Vaccination is slowing down, but there are 10 million doses in the freezer. It currently takes ~102 days for new deliveries to get into arms.

At the current rate, Canadians should achieve herd immunity around Dec-18 when 80% of the entire population is fully vaccinated. There is no approved vaccine for children aged 11 or younger.
